.TH SHELL 18th "May 2022" "ALX School" "Simple Shell man page"

.SH NAME
shell\fR \- UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
shell\fR [\fIfilename\fR]

.SH COPYRIGHT
shell is Copyright (C) 2022 by Brian Kiprotich and Mercy Mukiri

.SH DESCRIPTION
Shell\fR is a command language interpreter which executes commands read from a file or standard input.

.SH ARGUMENTS
The first argument is assumed to be the name of a file containing shell commands. Shell reads and executes commands from this file, then exits.

.SH Environment
When a program is invoked it is given an array of strings called the environment that consist a list of name-value pairs, of the form name=value.

.SH Exit Status
An exit status of zero indicates success. A non-zero exit status indicates failure.

.SH SEE ALSO
access(2), chdir(2), execve(2), \_exit(2), exit(3), fflush(3), fork(2), free(3), isatty(3), getcwd(3), malloc(3), open(2), read(2), sh(1), signal(2), stat(2), wait(2), write(2)

.SH AUTHORS
Brian Kiprotich and Mercy Mukiri
